summary: I see a lot of people “giving up” (?) on gay!Fjord in light of the Avantika Stuff™ but like,,,I’m over here more convinced than...
body: I see a lot of people “giving up” (?) on gay!Fjord in light of the Avantika Stuff™ but like,,,I’m over here more convinced than ever? Like idk if y’all ~remember the closet~ but Fjord’s desperate yet silent protests are EXACTLY how I remember feeling during my first two (and only thank gOD) het relationships. Praying someone would step in but at the same time trucking forward relentlessly. Awkwardly attempting to avoid actually doing anything but never saying no when things inevitably did start. Thinking that this is what. you. have. to. do. Like you do you…but this is a dark ass mirror for me !!

summary: I see you posting about critical roles. I dont know nothing about this, can you please explain me? I want to watch but dunno how...
question: I see you posting about critical roles. I dont know nothing about this, can you please explain me? I want to watch but dunno how to start and I know nothing about english voice actors (I'm brazilian) but I see all the hype and I want to know more
answer: Oh man, this was BURIED in my asks, sorry! Critical Role is a show where famous American voice actors who are friends sit down and play Dungeons and Dragons! It’s really as simple as that really. They are very funny, charismatic, and talented at what they do so it really adds to the storytelling experience of the D&D game they play! I’m not really sure what else I can say, I would just recommend giving campaign 2 a shot! And if you wanna start with 1, I suggest starting around episode 30 or something, the ones WITHOUT Orian, he ended up being an asshole and had to “leave” the show (he did something bad we don’t know about and got kicked out)

summary: ‪So I really don’t want to do this. But we’re really tight on money right now, and will be for the next couple weeks. My dad has...
body:
‪So I really don’t want to do this. But we’re really tight on money right now, and will be for the next couple weeks. My dad has a doctors appointment on Monday and I need to pay that bill. But I don’t know if we’ll have that and still be able to pay our insurance‬ on top of the other bills that are due. We’re three months behind on my parents’ insurance. And in danger of them dropping us. Im not looking for three months worth of insurance payments though. Just a little bit to help with one, and my dad’s $30 doctors bill.

I’m really worried about losing my parents insurance. They’re both in their 70s. My dad had cancer a couple years ago and needs monitoring to make sure it doesn’t come back. And my mom is a diabetic. They can’t go without insurance. I know money is tight for pretty much everyone, but if you can spare anything it would be appreciated. And even if you can’t, please pass this around so maybe someone else sees it and can spare something. Every little bit helps, even a signal boost.

PayPal: jolybeann / jolybeann@gmail
